parameters.name: PULSE_NUMBER
parameters.description: THE PULSE NUMBER FOR A GIVEN ORBIT, STARTING AT ZERO

parameters.name: EPHEMERIS_TIME
parameters.description: NUMBER OF SECONDS ELAPSED SINCE JAN, 1, 2000, 12:00 UTC CORRESPONDING TO THE TIME OF THE OBSERVATION

parameters.name: LOCAL_TRUE_SOLAR_TIME
parameters.description: ANGLE BETWEEN THE MERIDIAN PASSING THROUGH THE SUB-SPACECRAFT POINT AND THE MERIDIAN PASSING THROUGH THE SUBSOLAR POINT OF MARS, EXPRESSED ON A 24-HOURS CLOCK. 12.000 CORRESPONDS TO AN ANGLE OF 0 DEGREE, WHILE 00.000 CORRESPONDS TO AN ANGLE OF 180 DEGREES

parameters.name: X_SC_MSO
parameters.description: X COMPONENT OF THE POSITION VECTOR FROM MARS CENTER TO THE SPACECRAFT EXPRESSED IN MSO COORDINATES. +X POINTS FROM MARS TOWARD THE SUN +Y POINTS OPPOSITE TO THE ORBITAL MOTION OF MARS +Z COMPLETES THE RIGHT-HAND COORDINATES SYSTEM

parameters.name: Y_SC_MSO
parameters.description: Y COMPONENT OF THE POSITION VECTOR FROM MARS CENTER TO THE SPACECRAFT EXPRESSED IN MSO COORDINATES. +X POINTS FROM MARS TOWARD THE SUN +Y POINTS OPPOSITE TO THE ORBITAL MOTION OF MARS +Z COMPLETES THE RIGHT-HAND COORDINATES SYSTEM

parameters.name: Z_SC_MSO
parameters.description: Z COMPONENT OF THE POSITION VECTOR FROM MARS CENTER TO THE SPACECRAFT EXPRESSED IN MSO COORDINATES. +X POINTS FROM MARS TOWARD THE SUN +Y POINTS OPPOSITE TO THE ORBITAL MOTION OF MARS +Z COMPLETES THE RIGHT-HAND COORDINATES SYSTEM

parameters.name: SZA
parameters.description: ANGLE BETWEEN THE ZENITH AND THE APPARENT POSITION OF THE SUN. AT 0 THE SUN IS AT THE ZENITH AND 90 AT THE TERMINATOR

parameters.name: TEC
parameters.description: TOTAL ELECTRON CONTENT DERIVED FROM THE IONOSPHERE DISTORTION CORRECTION METHOD AS DESCRIBED IN MOUGINOT ET AL. 2008 (SEE THE DOCUMENT DIRECTORY)

parameters.name: A1
parameters.description: FIRST PARAMETER OF THE CORRECTION. SEE MOUGINOT ET AL. 2008 (IN THE DOCUMENT DIRECTORY)

parameters.name: A2
parameters.description: 2ND PARAMETER OF THE CORRECTION. SEE MOUGINOT ET AL. 2008 (IN THE DOCUMENT DIRECTORY)

parameters.name: A3
parameters.description: 3RD PARAMETER OF THE CORRECTION. SEE MOUGINOT ET AL. 2008 (IN THE DOCUMENT DIRECTORY)

parameters.name: FLAG
parameters.description: 0/1 : BELOW/ABOVE SIGNAL TO NOISE RATIO THRESHOLD. SEE MARSIS DERIVED ENHANCED IONOSPHERIC CALIBRATION DATA, TECHNICAL REPORT, VOL3.
